{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17502542","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17502542"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:45:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:45:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1871"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1871","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1871"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.14,0.52,0.02,0.27]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1871"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116464"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1871","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1871"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1871"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98463"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"380"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"968"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1391"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40001"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116464","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116464"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents with a two month of increasing weakness in his left thumb. He finds it increasingly difficult to grasp small objects between his thumb and forefinger. On examination, in addition to weakness of opposition of the left thumb, there is also some reduced sensation over the thumb and forefinger.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lateral epicondylitis","Prolapse of C5-6 disc","Carpal tunnel syndrome","Thoracic outlet syndrome","Anterior interosseous nerve lesion"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s symptoms are almost certainly due to median nerve compression (in the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecarpal tunnel\u003C/strong\u003E). The median nerve innervates the abductor pollicis brevis and opponens pollicis muscles and the sensory aspect of the thumb, index, middle and part of the ring fingers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral epicondylitis \u003C/strong\u003Eis an overuse syndrome of the extensor tendons in the forearm and presents with symptoms of pain at the lateral elbow, which can be activity related.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProlapse of a C5-6 disc\u003C/strong\u003E would present with symptoms over the C5 \u0026amp; C6 dermatomes, for example pain or tingling over the thumb and can also present with neck pain. These patients would also be likely to experience biceps weakness and wrist extension weakness.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThoracic outlet syndrome \u003C/strong\u003Eoccurs when there is compression of the brachial plexus and or subclavian vessels. It can present with non-specific pain and tingling in the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnterior interosseous nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is a terminal branch of the median nerve and a lesion in this nerve results in motor paralysis of the muscles innervated by this nerve. It supplies flexor pollicis longus, pronator quadratus, and the lateral half of the flexor digitorum profundus.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Weakness of the thumb is a common sequela of carpal tunnel syndrome."],"references":["Wipperman, J. and Goerl, K., 2016.\u00a0Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: Diagnosis And Management. [online] Aafp.org.","Kuhn JE, Lebus V GF, Bible JE. Thoracic outlet syndrome. J Am Acad Orthop Surg. 2015 Apr;23(4):222-32. doi: 10.5435/JAAOS-D-13-00215. PMID: 25808686.","Rodner CM, Tinsley BA, O\u0027Malley MP. Pronator syndrome and anterior interosseous nerve syndrome. J Am Acad Orthop Surg. 2013 May;21(5):268-75. doi: 10.5435/JAAOS-21-05-268. PMID: 23637145.","Cervical Radiculopathy: A Common Cause of Neck Pain [Internet]. Aafp.org. 2016 [cited 31 January 2021]. Available from: https://www.aafp.org/afp/2016/0501/p746-s1.html"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98463"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1871"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98463","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98463"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-29T10:33:17+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-29T10:33:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1871"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116464"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"